text:
"Oh no, Trump has broken the world trade order and depression is inevitable, but also -- hahaha -- he's cucked on tariffs and nothing has happened." 
-- Seeing so much of this commentary my head is spinning.
... Part of this is that serious diplomacy -- whether on trade or anything else -- is substantially non-public by essence, and this is messing with people's minds. ...
... The residual question is whether you think Trump II is capable of serious diplomacy. Both sides on this probably require more patience than they're immediately disposed to offer. ...
... "Wild, but ultimately very serious" is my default.
You mean, "He should tell me clearly what he wants," but you can see why he can't.
Stuff was just sludging along at their level before. It felt like involvement.
Balanced.
These guys are all-in, I'm still split-brained.
Cowen at his best. thefp.com/p/17th-century-eng…
... Alternative sample. marginalrevolution.com/margi…

It's not that Capital is just robots and always has been ... but it roughly is. 
So who -- or what -- has the robots?
They're winning modernity.
Yes, the snark is all "Hahaha, America has totally deindustrialized! No way you can reindustrialize from there."
This is also my impression.
Homeless blackpill addicts littering the timeline is just the cost of modern urban life.
And they will have them.
A by now very good, and asymptotically convergent proxy, yes.
If Trump was visibly sweating and drooling, while roaring "America is going to have ALL the robots!" he'd still be the most strategically promising US President of my lifetime.
Sure, 'robots' abbreviates 'full-robotics supply chains' (as it should out of theoretical coherence).
Systematic schismatics under The Invisible Hands.
Really makes you think.
"If there was simply no politics my entire life's work would make sense."
Actually, they totally won't.
You of course have to say that.
Saddam and Gonoreah all over the place.
Out of respect for Kindness to Losers and Haters Month I'm going to be on an X hiatus for a couple of days.
